<xref:System.Windows.Controls.ItemsControl.ItemsSource%2A> property of the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.ListBox> to `BookTable` of the `DataSet`:  \n  \n [!code-xml[ADODataSet#2](../../../../samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_Wpf/ADODataSet/CSharp/Window1.xaml#2)]  \n  \n `BookItemTemplate` is the <xref:System.Windows.DataTemplate> that defines how the data appears:  \n  \n [!code-xml[ADODataSet#3](../../../../samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_Wpf/ADODataSet/CSharp/Window1.xaml#3)]  \n  \n The `IntColorConverter` converts an `int` to a color. With the use of this converter, the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBlock.Background%2A> color of the third <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBlock> appears green if the value of `NumPages` is less than 350 and red otherwise. The implementation of the converter is not shown here.  \n  \n## See Also  \n <xref:System.Windows.Data.BindingListCollectionView>   \n [Data Binding Overview](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/data/data-binding-overview.md)   \n [How-to Topics](../../../../docs/framework/wpf/data/data-binding-how-to-topics.md)","nodes":[{"pos":[12,67],"content":"How to: Bind to an ADO.NET Data Source | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"How to: Bind to an ADO.NET Data Source | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,55]}]},{"pos":[527,565],"content":"How to: Bind to an ADO.NET Data Source","linkify":"How to: Bind to an ADO.NET Data Source","nodes":[{"content":"How to: Bind to an ADO.NET Data Source","pos":[0,38]}]},{"pos":[566,816],"content":"This example shows how to bind a <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_winclient](../../../../includes/tlasharptla-winclient-md.md)]</ph> <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.ListBox&gt;</ph> control to an <ph id=\"ph3\">[!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_adonet](../../../../includes/tlasharptla-adonet-md.md)]</ph> <ph id=\"ph4\">`DataSet`</ph>.","source":"This example shows how to bind a [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_winclient](../../../../includes/tlasharptla-winclient-md.md)] <